{{Infobox mountain
| name = Yumura-yama
| photo = [[File:Mt.Yumura 201122.jpg|300px|]]
| photo_caption = Viewed from the Kofu City Midorigaoka Sports Park Athletic Stadium
| elevation_m = 446
| coordinates = {{Coord|35|41|02|N|138|33|07|E|type:mountain_region:JP-19|display=inline,title}}
| location = {{JPN}}<br />{{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県}}, {{ill|Kofu|ja|甲府市}}
| range = {{ill|Okuchichibu Mountains|ja|奥秩父山塊}}
| type = {{ill|Mountain massif|ja|山塊}}
| map = {{Location map|Japan Mapplot|coordinates={{Coord|35.6692|138.6256}}|caption=|width=300}}<small>Location of Yumura-yama</small>
}}
'''Yumura-yama''' (湯村山) is a {{ill|mountain|ja|山}} located in {{ill|Kofu|ja|甲府市}}, {{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県}}, Japan, at the southern tip of the {{ill|Okuchichibu Mountains|ja|奥秩父山塊}}. It has an elevation of 446 meters and is one of the {{ill|Kofu Meizan|ja|甲府名山}}.

== Overview ==
Located approximately 1.8 km northwest of {{ill|Kofu Station|ja|甲府駅}} on the {{ill|Chuo Main Line|ja|中央本線}}, Yumura-yama offers a panoramic view of Kofu City from its summit. The hiking trails are well-maintained, with sections paved with asphalt, making them popular among local residents. From the trailhead near {{ill|Midorigaoka Sports Park|ja|甲府市緑が丘スポーツ公園}}, it takes about 20 minutes to reach the junction leading to the Yumura-yama summit and the {{ill|Chiyoda Lake|ja|千代田湖}} area. The summit is a further 10 minutes from the junction. Another route starts from Yumura Town.<ref>[https://kofu-tourism.com/course/546 甲府観光ナビ 湯村山をハイキングしよう！]</ref>

== History ==
In 1523 ({{ill|Daiei era|ja|大永}} 3), {{ill|Takeda Nobutora|ja|武田信虎}} constructed a mountain fortress (Yumura-yama Castle) at the summit. Its location allowed for extensive surveillance and intelligence gathering over the Kofu Basin. Today, remnants such as a well and some minor ruins remain, alongside a reconstructed beacon fire platform ({{ill|Noroshi|ja|狼煙}}). The hiking trail also features several {{ill|Cairn tombs|ja|積石塚}} along the way.<ref>[https://www.city.kofu.yamanashi.jp/senior/kamejii/064.html 甲府市公式サイト内 湯村山にお城があった！？]</ref>

== Neighboring Mountains ==
* {{ill|Hosenji-yama|ja|法泉寺山}}
* {{ill|Hachioji-yama|ja|八王子山}}

== Related Topics ==
* {{ill|Okuchichibu Mountains|ja|奥秩父山塊}}
* {{ill|Kofu Meizan|ja|甲府名山}}
* {{ill|Chiyoda Lake|ja|千代田湖}}
* {{ill|Midorigaoka Sports Park|ja|甲府市緑が丘スポーツ公園}}

== Onsen ==
* {{ill|Shingen-no-Yu Yumura Onsen|ja|信玄の湯 湯村温泉}}

