In 1523 ({{ill|Daiei era|ja|大永|12=draft|12=draft}} 3), {{ill|Takeda Nobutora|ja|武田信虎|12=draft|12=draft}} constructed a mountain fortress (Yumura-yama Castle) at the summit. Its location allowed for extensive surveillance and intelligence gathering over the Kofu Basin. Today, remnants such as a well and some minor ruins remain, alongside a reconstructed beacon fire platform ({{ill|Noroshi|ja|狼煙|12=draft|12=draft}}). The hiking trail also features several {{ill|Cairn tombs|ja|積石塚|12=draft|12=draft}} along the way.<ref>[https://www.city.kofu.yamanashi.jp/senior/kamejii/064.html 甲府市公式サイト内 湯村山にお城があった！？]</ref>

