'''Yumura-yama''' (湯村山) is a [[:en:Mountain|mountain]] located in [[:en:Kōfu|Kofu]], [[:en:Yamanashi Prefecture|Yamanashi Prefecture]], Japan, at the southern tip of the [[:en:Okuchichibu Mountains|Okuchichibu Mountains]]. It has an elevation of 446 meters and is one of the {{ill|Kofu Meizan|ja|甲府名山|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofu Meizan|qq=}}.

== Overview ==
Located approximately 1.8 km northwest of [[:en:Kōfu Station|Kofu Station]] on the [[:en:Chūō Main Line|Chuo Main Line]], Yumura-yama offers a panoramic view of Kofu City from its summit. The hiking trails are well-maintained, with sections paved with asphalt, making them popular among local residents. From the trailhead near [[:en:Kofu Midorigaoka Sports Park Stadium|Midorigaoka Sports Park]], it takes about 20 minutes to reach the junction leading to the Yumura-yama summit and the {{ill|Chiyoda Lake|ja|千代田湖|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiyoda Lake|qq=}} area. The summit is a further 10 minutes from the junction. Another route starts from Yumura Town.<ref>[https://kofu-tourism.com/course/546 甲府観光ナビ 湯村山をハイキングしよう！]</ref>

== History ==
In 1523 ([[:en:Daiei (era)|Daiei era]] 3), [[:en:Takeda Nobutora|Takeda Nobutora]] constructed a mountain fortress (Yumura-yama Castle) at the summit. Its location allowed for extensive surveillance and intelligence gathering over the Kofu Basin. Today, remnants such as a well and some minor ruins remain, alongside a reconstructed beacon fire platform ([[:en:Smoke signal|Noroshi]]). The hiking trail also features several {{ill|Cairn tombs|ja|積石塚|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Cairn tombs|qq=}} along the way.<ref>[https://www.city.kofu.yamanashi.jp/senior/kamejii/064.html 甲府市公式サイト内 湯村山にお城があった！？]</ref>

